OL,3,CPip and universal credit cuts: Who
OL,4,Cwill be hit and how much will they
OL,5,Close?
OL,7,FFor example, an individual who needs
OL,8,Fhelp washing their hair or their body
OL,9,Fbelow the waist would score two points
OL,10,Fand therefore no longer qualify, but
OL,11,Fneeding help washing between the
OL,12,Fshoulders and waist is worth four
OL,13,Fpoints, meaning that would make
OL,14,Fsomeone eligible.
OL,16,FPeople claiming the daily living
OL,17,Fcomponent receive either a standard
OL,18,Frate of #72.65 a week, or an enhanced
OL,19,Frate of #108.55 a week, depending on
OL,20,Fthe severity of their condition.
