OL,3,CPip and universal credit cuts: Who
OL,4,Cwill be hit and how much will they
OL,5,Close?
OL,7,FIf all opposition parties vote against
OL,8,Fthe bill, only 83 Labour MPs need to
OL,9,Fjoin them for it to be defeated. If
OL,10,Fthe Conservatives decide to support
OL,11,Fthe reforms, that could give the
OL,12,Fgovernment a way out - but they have
OL,13,Finsisted on near-impossible conditions
OL,14,Fin return for their support.
OL,16,FKemi Badenoch said the Tories would
OL,17,Flend the government votes to pass the
OL,18,Flegislation but only if Labour rules
OL,19,Fout tax rises in the autumn budget as
OL,20,Fwell as reducing unemployment and
OL,21,Flowering the welfare budget.
