OL,7,FRumours swirled in Westminster on
OL,8,FWednesday that the government might
OL,9,Fpull the bill, but the prime minister
OL,10,Finsisted MPs will vote on the reforms
OL,11,Fnext week as planned, dismissing the
OL,12,Frebellion as "noises off".
OL,14,FAsked if he has "failed to read the
OL,15,Fmood" among Labour MPs, Starmer said:
OL,16,F"There's a pretty united front that
OL,17,Fsay we need reform... the question is
OL,18,Fhow is that reform is carried out."
